{
  "message": "test(conformance): dataframe groupby OHLC packet (FP-P2D-110)\n\nAdds conformance coverage for `DataFrame.groupby().ohlc()` \u2014 one of the\nfinancial-data helpers pandas ships that produces per-group\nopen/high/low/close aggregates. Pairs with the existing kurtosis /\nskew / sem groupby packets already registered in earlier commits.\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/src/lib.rs\n  * New `#[test] packet_filter_runs_dataframe_groupby_ohlc_packet`\n    calls `run_packet_by_id(&cfg, \"FP-P2D-110\",\n    OracleMode::FixtureExpected)` and asserts:\n      - `report.packet_id == Some(\"FP-P2D-110\")`\n      - `report.fixture_count >= 3` (three fixtures registered\n        in the next bullet)\n      - `report.is_green()` \u2014 all fixtures match SciPy/pandas\n        oracle bytes.\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/fixtures/packets/\n  * New fixtures encoded in the standard FP-P2D packet shape:\n      - fp_p2d_110_dataframe_groupby_ohlc_basic_strict.json\n        Strict-mode basic case: 6-row DataFrame grouped on one\n        key, single numeric column, expected output is the 4-col\n        (open, high, low, close) tuple per group.\n      - fp_p2d_110_dataframe_groupby_ohlc_multi_group_hardened.json\n        Hardened-mode case with three groups, NaN-interleaved\n        values, tests that NaN rows are correctly excluded from\n        OHLC calcs.\n      - fp_p2d_110_dataframe_groupby_ohlc_single_value_strict.json\n        Edge case: every group has exactly one row, so O=H=L=C.\n        Catches implementations that treat single-row groups as\n        degenerate.\n\nNo runtime-code change in this commit \u2014 the fp-conformance test\nharness already supports arbitrary packet ids.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
